-- Sweden Said to Plan Issue of 20-Year Bonds for Exchange
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-03-12T10:36:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/sweden-said-to-plan-issue-of-20-year-bonds-for-exchange.html
Sweden hired banks to arrange an
exchange of existing bonds into new 20-year notes in krona,
according to a banker involved in the deal.  Barclays Capital, Danske Bank AS,  Svenska Handelsbanken ,
 Nordea Bank AB (NDA) , Nykredit Bank AS, Royal Bank of Scotland Group
Plc, SEB and  Swedbank AB (SWEDA)  are managing the transaction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah Benjamin in London at 
 hbenjamin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Shanahan at 
 mshanahan3@bloomberg.net  